OL,3,CGovernment may restrict jury trials
OL,4,Cfor only the most serious cases
OL,6,FAccording to the paper, Lammy wrote in
OL,7,Fa briefing note to other ministers and
OL,8,Fsenior civil servants this month that
OL,9,Frape, murder, manslaughter and "public
OL,10,Finterest" cases would be heard by
OL,11,Fjuries, while other lower offences
OL,12,Fwould be heard by a judge.
OL,14,FThe move comes as the Government is
OL,15,Fyet to respond to recommendations made
OL,16,Fby Sir Brian Leveson in a review of
OL,17,Fhow to reform the court system and cut
OL,18,Fthe record-high crown court backlog.
