OL,3,CGovernment may restrict jury trials
OL,4,Cfor only the most serious cases
OL,6,FUnder Sir Brian's recommendations,
OL,7,Fjuries would be reserved to hear the
OL,8,Fmost serious cases, while other cases
OL,9,Fwould be diverted to magistrates'
OL,10,Fcourts or to the proposed Crown Court
OL,11,FBench Division for trials to be heard
OL,12,Fby judges.
OL,14,FProposals to restrict jury trials have
OL,15,Falready met resistance from legal
OL,16,Fprofessionals.
OL,18,FThe Bar Council said, "There is no
OL,19,Fneed to curtail the right to a trial
OL,20,Fby jury - from both a principle and
OL,21,Fpractical position".
