OL,3,CGovernment may restrict jury trials
OL,4,Cfor only the most serious cases
OL,6,FMeanwhile, nearly three-quarters of
OL,7,Fsolicitors surveyed by the Law Society
OL,8,Fof England and Wales said they were
OL,9,Fconcerned about jury trials being
OL,10,Fremoved.
OL,12,FIn his review, Sir Brian said reform
OL,13,Fof jury trials was "merited" to
OL,14,Faddress problems, particularly with
OL,15,Flengthy or complex trials.
OL,17,F"Reform to address these concerns will
OL,18,Fbe likely to have positive impacts in
OL,19,Fterms of efficiency, by reducing the
OL,20,Fopen caseload, and, in addition, in
OL,21,Fterms of financial savings," he said.
